<HEADLINE> Yemeni President Alleges Saudi Arabia Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
claimed Monday that three Yemeni were killed and nine wounded in a
military attack launched by Saudi Arabia navy Sunday on a Yemeni
island in the Red Sea.
</P>
<P>
Nine Saudi naval vessels took part in the aggression with
long-range artillery that resulted in the death of three Yemeni
and wounding of nine, the president told a news conference in
Sanaa.
</P>
<P>
Saleh accused Saudi Arabia of trying to change demarcation
lines by force to grab territory from Yemen. The territory dispute
between the two countries dates back 60 years.
</P>
<P>
The attack stopped later Sunday after Yemen contacted the Saudi
government, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Saleh said Yemen's Foreign Minister, Abdul-Qader Bagammal,
would fly to Saudi Arabia to discuss the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
