<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Launch Nationwide Campaign against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe embarks on a nationwide
campaign this week to introduce the 70-million-U.S. Dollar
community action project meant to improve living standards in
rural areas.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Public Service, Labour and Social
Welfare, the project, which is being financed by the World Bank,
is a component of the Zimbabwean government's poverty alleviation
action program and is administered through the social dimensions
fund. It will be implemented over five years, the daily Herald
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The project is targeted toward the country's 26 poorest
districts and seeks to strengthen the capacity of rural
communities, promote participatory and collaborative planning and
the implementation of projects through community partnership with
rural district councils, non-governmental organisations, the
government and private sector.
</P>
<P>
The poverty alleviation action plan was adopted in 1994 to
reduce poverty caused mainly by unemployment through
income-generating program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
