<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A British aid worker was shot
dead during a robbery on a bar in the Kenyan capital on Sunday
night, local sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The dead, identified Colin Baker, was the assistant director
for the regional office of the London-based Action Aid, the
Action Aid said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Police said Baker, 45, was killed by three robbers -- one
armed with a pistol -- who raided Papa Locos Bar &AMP; Restaurant in
the rich Westlands suburb around 10:00 p.m..
</P>
<P>
The gunmen, speaking in Kiswahili, ordered customers to lie on
the floor, but Baker didn't understand and was shot.
</P>
<P>
He died on the way to hospital, said the police. No one else
was hurt.
</P>
<P>
The robbers escaped with 74,000 Shillings (about 1,245 U.S.
Dollars) taken from the bar's cash office, police said. 
