<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Recommends UNIFIL Mandate Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 20 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan Monday recommended the extension of the mandate of the
United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL) for a further
period of six months until January 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Security Council, Annan said that during
the past six months, fighting in south Lebanon continued and
civilians were again put at risk, although the number of those who
were killed decreased.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that while the UNIFIL continues its efforts to limit
the conflict and to protect the inhabitants from the fighting, the
situation in the area remains volatile and continues to give cause
for serious concern.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief said the UNIFIL's contribution to stability and
the protection it provides to the population of the area remain
important. He, therefore, recommended the extension of the mandate
of the UNIFIL. 
