Although the chief U.N. arms inspector Richard Butler said he
had no doubt of the findings, the United Nations agreed to take
samples for further testing in laboratories in France and
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi radio political editor said it were the U.S. troops
that used chemical and napalm bombs in the Vietnam War, and in the
Gulf War, U.S. and British troops used depleted uranium bombs
against the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
While advocating non-proliferation of mass destruction weapons,
the U.S. government itself helped Israel to build large nuclear,
biological, chemical and hydrogen arsenals, said the editor. 
