according to its own rhythm" and that the primary signs of change
given by Nigeria since Abukabar succeeded General Sani Abacha as
the chief of state in June were "very positive."
</P>
<P>
He said that France would plead for within the EU a gradual
lifting of the sanctions.
</P>
<P>
"We have the confidence in the will of General Abukabar to
carry forward the democratic process which will allow Nigerians to
choose their government within a reasonable duration of time from
now," he said.
</P>
<P>
The United States and the EU imposed sanctions on Nigeria in
1993 after the Nigerian military canceled the result of a
presidential election.
</P>
<P>
