Nigeria's new leader after the sudden death of Abacha on June 8.
</P>
<P>
As part of his national reconciliation effort, Abubakar has
ordered the release of 26 coup plotters, opposition leaders and
journalists.
</P>
<P>
He also ordered the release of all prisoners who have
completed their jail terms but remained behind the bar, to
decongest the country's cells and show his will to protect human
rights.
</P>
<P>
Also according to the NTA, Abubakar is expected to make his
long-awaited national broadcast Monday at 9:00 p.m. (local time)
on his plan to return Nigeria to civil rule, after 13 straight
years of military government.  
