<HEADLINE> Largest Development Zone in Ethnic Minority Area Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- China's largest development zone
in an ethnic minority area, the Qianjiang Development Zone, will
soon be operational.
</P>
<P>
The zone, located in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality,
covers an area of 1.69 square kilometers, and is densely populated
by ethnic minority groups. Of the total population of 2.84
million, 73.5 percent are people of ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
According to an eight-year plan recently revealed by Liu Xuepu
(of ethnic Tu group), director of the zone's administrative
committee, the daily needs of the people living in the zone will
be fully provided by the year 2000, and their overall economic
well-being will be realized by 2005.
</P>
<P>
As part of the plan, the zone is expected to achieve a 14.9
percent GDP growth rate, with 3 billion yuan (361 million US
dollars) in agricultural output and 1.42 billion yuan in township
enterprise output this year.
</P>
<P>
The Qianjiang region has favorable natural conditions including
a vast grassland, and abounds with manganese, bauxite and mercury.
</P>
</TEXT>
