<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Decides to Curb Import of Luxury Items </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government has
decided to curb import of luxury items for balance of payments
purposes.
</P>
<P>
Announcing a package of measures here Tuesday at a press
conference, Finance Minister Sartaj Aziz said that a regulatory
custom duty of 100 percent is being levied on import of four-wheel
vehicles, including Pajero and Land Cruisers, and on cars above
1,800 c.c.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the initial registration fee will be increased by
200,000 rupees (46 rupees to one U.S. dollar) on Mercedes Benz,
BMW and other luxury vehicles up to 2,000 c.c. and 400,000 rupees
on such vehicles beyond 2,000 c.c.
</P>
<P>
The initial registration fee for vehicles with engine capacity
of 2,500 c.c. or above will be 300,000 rupees.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the finance minister also announced measures to
prevent the flight of capital.
</P>
<P>
"It is unfortunate that at this critical time some people have
been working against the national interests and sending the scarce
foreign exchange abroad," Aziz noted.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot allow this practice to continue," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said that restrictions are being imposed, until further
orders, on carrying abroad more than 10,000 dollars without prior
written approval of the Sate Bank of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
All unlicensed money changers are being asked to register with
the State Bank of Pakistan within one month. They will then be
granted licenses provided they meet the criteria of the bank.
</P>
<P>
Aziz believed that the steps, which are being taken, will
stabilize the exchange market, boost exports and remittances and
curb non-essential imports.
</P>
<P>
"Success in this area is crucial if we are to meet the
challenge of sanctions, while preventing any disruption of
economic activity within the country and avoiding inflation in the
prices of essential commodities," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
