<P>
-- The coffin of Nkaw-Isi-Isi, ruler of upper Egypt in the era
of Titi I, King of the sixth dynasty 4,500 years ago, has been
discovered.
</P>
<P>
A joint team, grouping experts from the Suez Canal University
and the Australian University of Maccury have found the coffin of
the ruler recently, 14 years after the discovery of his tomb in
1984.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said Monday that the
Egyptian-French initiative for an international conference on the
stalled Middle East peace process dovetails with the U.S. proposal
calling for a 13 percent Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Moussa will visit Paris next week to discuss with his French
counterpart details of the initiative, which was put forward in
May.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- The Environment Affairs Agency has completed an
environment-friendly atlas containing information and guidelines
which facilitate the tourism development ventures along the Red
Sea coast to observe environment regulations.
</P>
<P>
The new atlas, financed by the U.N. Environment Program, is
part of a project seeking to manage the Red Sea coastal
resources. 
</P>
