<HEADLINE> Festina Manager Allegedly Organized Slush Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The drugs scandal hitting the Tour de France took
another turn on Tuesday when the Festina team manager allegedly ordered his
riders to contribute to a fund for illegal substances.
</P>
<P>
The team doctor Eric Ryckaert claimed that the riders were obliged to put
part of their win bonuses into a `black box' fund to buy banned substances.
</P>
<P>
Team manager Bruno Roussel was in charge of the system and riders decided
what substances they wanted to take, Arsene Ryckaert said.
</P>
<P>
The drug scandal has rocked the Tour de France since customs officers found
illegal substances in the car of the physiotherapist of Festina's top rider
Richard Virenque.
</P>
<P>
The Festina team was thrown out of the race Saturday and police in the
northern city of Lille are holding Ryckaert and Roussel.  
