<HEADLINE> Teleconference Rewards Model Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A national teleconference was held
in the Chinese capital today to reward 14 enterprises for their
meritorious deeds.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises included the Handan Steel Group Co. Ltd., the
Zhenhai Oil Refinery And Chemical Shareholding Co. Ltd., the
Yanzhou Mining (Group) Co. Ltd., and the Daqing Petroleum
Administration.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji attended the conference, while Vice-Premier
Li Lanqing delivered an address urging all localities and
industries to follow suit and do a better job in the next half of
this year in order to realize the year's reform and development
goals.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, China in the first half of the year increased
domestic demand; boosted exports and tried to introduce more
foreign capital; further readjusted economic structure to promote
steady growth in industrial and agricultural production; and
pushed forwards economic reform by adopting a number of major
reform measures.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier outlined the tasks for the second half of the
year. They include further expanding domestic demand by adopting
a more active financial policy; stepping up efforts to build
infrastructure; carefully handling the issue of state factory
layoffs and re-employment; deepening the reform in the grain
circulation system and bolstering the steady and sustained growth
of agriculture; pushing forwards enterprise reform and development
for the stable growth of industrial production; stepping up
efforts in taxation and improving financial services; trying to
boost exports and imports and making greater efforts to introduce
more overseas capital; cracking down on smuggling activities;
making every effort to increase the domestic demands for consumer
goods; and furthering in anti-flood efforts.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the key to fulfilling the tasks for the second
half of the year is the implementation of all the policies and
measures of the central government as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The conference was presided over by Vice-Premier Wu
Bangguo. Also present were Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao, State
Councilor Luo Gan, and leading officials from central government
departments, state banks, major state-owned companies, and
provincial and prefectural governments.
</P>
</TEXT>
