<HEADLINE> E. African Union Aims to Benefit People: Ugandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
explained that the East African Union should be one of the people
instead of one of the government or the leaders, because it is
aimed to benefit people.
</P>
<P>
He made the explanation of the union he put forth at last
week's national conference of the National Resistance Movement,
at a press conference in State House, Nakasero Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that the union should provide freedom of movement and
employment for the people. Within the union, people of any of the
member countries can travel to neighboring states without
passports and they can do business there, he added.
</P>
<P>
The true meaning of union lies in free communication and real
integration in both political and economic fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
Museveni said economic integration in the region has already
begun because there are already many kinds of cooperation in the
economic sector.
</P>
<P>
He put forth the notion of the union when analysing the causes
of backwardness of Africa at the national conference of the
ruling National Resistance Movement. He said one of main things
responsible for the backwardness is political fragmentation.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the states in the region and even in the whole
continent should be united politically and economically. This is
the only way "for a state to avoid subjugation and heavy
dependence on others," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The European Union is a good example for Africans to follow,
he told the conference delegates.
</P>
<P>
In Uganda, he suggested that tribalism or the notion of clan
should not be so stressed as previously. Union can produce
independence, and independence can eventually to promote economic
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
