<HEADLINE> Manila Plans to Further Liberalize Telecom Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investors may be allowed to
increase equity in the Philippines' telecommunications firms as
the government is planning to further liberalize the industry, a
senior government official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Transportation Undersecretary Josefina Lichauco said that the
transportation department is looking at the possibility of
allowing foreign investors to own more than 40 percent of a
telecommunications firm.
</P>
<P>
She pointed out that the telecom industry, which formed the
centerpiece of the previous administration's liberalization
policy, would benefit from the increased foreign equity to sustain
its capital-intensive nature.
</P>
<P>
Lichauco said she is drafting a report on the liberalization of
the industry. The report will be submitted to Transportation
Secretary Vicente Rivera for approval. 
</P>
