<HEADLINE> Brake Failure Caused Horror Bus Crash in South </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The bus that overturned and
killed 15 people in South Africa on Monday night had brake failure
seconds before it crashed, police said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"I have interviewed the driver who said his brakes failed
completely before the crash. He said he tried to control the bus but
failed, resulting in it rolling over," South African Press Association
quoted police spokesman Xolani Mbanyana as saying.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened on the Umtata-Port St Johns Road in
Eastern Cape Province. Earlier reports said the accident
happened Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen people died on the spot and another died on his way to
hospital. The 15th victim died in hospital. Seventy-nine people were
wounded.
</P>
<P>
The condition of two critically injured patients transferred to
Umtata General Hospital was not immediately known.  
</P>
