<HEADLINE> National Ballet of China To Perform in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The National Ballet of China
will perform two classical ballets, Giselle and The Red Detachment
of Women, in Hong Kong this week.
</P>
<P>
The National Ballet of China, founded in 1959, is China's sole
national ballet company. It staged performances here in 1994
and 1997.
</P>
<P>
"The company values outstanding classical ballets, with a solid
foundation of classical ballet style laid by celebrated Russian
ballet master Pyotr Gusev," director of the company Zhao Ruheng
told a press conference Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The dancers of the National Ballet are all graduates from the
Beijing Dance Academy, with years' professional training, many of
who have been awarded medals at international competitions, the
veteran dancer said.
</P>
<P>
Popular French classical ballet Giselle, the legendary story of
a beautiful and innocent peasant girl who falls in love with a
Count, will be staged Wednesday and Thursday at the Grand Theater
of the Hong Kong Cultural Center.
</P>
<P>
A well-known piece created by Chinese artists -- The Red
Detachment of Women -- is scheduled for Friday and Saturday. It
tells the story of a poor peasant's daughter, Wu Qinghua, who is
persecuted by a roguish landowner and later joins the Red
Detachment of Women of the Army.
</P>
<P>
The National Ballet will go to Macao following its performance
in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
