<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's gold and foreign
exchange and other reserves held by Bank Negara (central bank),
including special drawing rights, dropped according to a statement
from the central bank here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The reserves went down to 57,640.491 million ringgit (14,024.45
million U.S. dollars) as at July 15, 1998 from 58,204.820 million
ringgit (14,161.756 million U.S. dollars) registered on June 30,
1998, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The central bank's total assets and liabilities fell to
85,228.976 million ringgit (20,736.977 million U.S. dollars) from
89,037.915 million ringgit (21,663.726 million U.S. dollars)
during the period under review.
</P>
<P>
Loans and advances increased to 5,823.047 million ringgit
(1,416.799 million U.S. dollars) from 5,756.394 million ringgit
(1,400.582 million U.S. dollars) during the same period. 
</P>
