<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The market was quiet with most players staying on the sidelines
and focus continued to be on major blue chips which saw their
gains made last Friday wiped out on profit taking.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 7.46
points to 437.82, the all-share Emas Index fell 1.68 points to
110.06, the Industrial Index lost 3.97 points to 909.37 and the
Second Board was down by 1.10 points to 92.34.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 412 to 109, 142 counters were unchanged,
259 untraded and 45 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover declined to 103.729 million shares valued at
202.464 million ringgit (49.261 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 117.384 million shares valued at 227.048 million ringgit
(55.242 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume fell to 100.458 million shares valued at
198.079 million ringgit (48.194 million U.S. dollars) from 112.950
million shares worth 221.916 million ringgit (53.994 million U.S.
dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover decreased to 3.272 million shares
worth 4.384 million ringgit (1.066 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 4.434 million shares valued at 5.851 million ringgit
(1.423 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, off market deals increased to 6.781 million shares
valued at 16.264 million ringgit (3.957 million U.S. dollars) from
2.333 million shares worth 5.566 million ringgit (1.354 million
U.S. dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.793
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 7.913
million shares, construction 17.696 million shares,
trading/services 36.435 million shares, infrastructure 628,000
shares, finance 16.296 million shares, hotels 191,000 shares,
properties 7.531 million shares, plantation 2.030 million shares,
mining 501,000 shares, trusts 46,000 shares, closed/fund 67,000
shares and loans 6.330 million shares. 
</P>
