<HEADLINE> HongKongBank Awarded Best Foreign Bank in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong and Shanghai
Banking Corporation Limited (HongKongBank) has been awarded the
Best Foreign Bank in China for the second year by Euromoney which
announced the award in its July 1998 issue.
</P>
<P>
Eddie Wang, head of China Business at HongKongBank, said: "we
are delighted that HongKongBank has, once again, been ranked the
best foreign bank in the Chinese mainland."
</P>
<P>
"This is another affirmation of HongKongBank's outstanding
performance in the Chinese mainland, and an enormous encouragement
to our commitment to further expand our business" there, he said.
</P>
<P>
HongKongBank has now a mainland network of eight branches in
Beijing, Dalian, Qingdao, Shanghai, Shenzhen, Tianjin, Wuhan and
Xiamen, a sub-branch in Puxi, Shanghai, and two representative
offices in Chengdu and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The network has a staff of over 600, the majority of whom were
recruited in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
With its headquarters in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, HongKongBank has also been awarded the Best Bank in Hong
Kong, Best Bank in Asia by Euromoney.
</P>
<P>
HongKongBank, together with its subsidiaries, has more than 600
offices in 32 countries and regions in the world.
</P>
<P>
It is a principal member of the HSBC Group which, with more
than 5,500 offices in 81 countries and regions and assets in
excess of 471 billion U.S. dollars as at December 31, 1997, is
among the world's largest banking and financial services
institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
