<HEADLINE> Eight More Die of Snake Bite in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people have died
of snake bite in the past few days in Kailali and Syangja
districts, the Kantipur Daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Seven people including children died last Friday in Kailali
district, far western Nepal, while one died in Syangja district in
the western part of the country, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
So far about 25 people have succumbed to snake bite in the
country during the summer season.
</P>
<P>
Poisonous snakes like cobra and krait pose a serious threat to
both human being and livestock in the Himalayan kingdom,
especially during the monsoon season which lasts from June to
September. 
</P>
