<HEADLINE> Cambodia: Security Personnel to Be Deployed for Polling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 21 (Xinhua) -- There will be 95,000 security
personnel, including police, military police and soldiers, to
ensure the security of the polling station, Cambodia's National
Election Committee (NEC) announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The security forces, commanded by the NEC sub-committee on
security, are available to election officials at the levels of
province, district, commune and polling station.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there is also an intervention force under the
command of the NEC sub-committee on security, which can respond
quickly to any possible serious trouble.
</P>
<P>
Five security personnel will be deployed at each polling
station, all wearing civilian clothes and white identity cards.
</P>
<P>
There will be two unarmed guards posted 40 meters from each
polling station, and three more guards 200 to 250 meters away with
one AK-47 rifle kept out of sight to avoid causing scares among
the voters.
</P>
<P>
Friday's attacks on electoral officials northeast of Anlong
Veng has caused concern over the security of the election.
</P>
<P>
Senior election officials in Phnom Penh later pledged that they
would not allow the attack to deter the polls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
