<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan MPs Call For SAARC to Protect Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Some Sri Lankan parliamentarians
have called for the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) to set up an organization to protect children
in the South Asian region, informed sources here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC, which groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the
Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka, is due to hold its 10th
summit in Colombo at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 Sri Lankan parliamentarians representing both the
government and the opposition were united in calling for a
separate ministry in the country to look into issues affecting
children, the sources quoted president of the lobby Jayalath
Jayawardena as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said they ask the SAARC to have a mechanism to ensure that
the declarations to protect the rights of children, which were
issued at the previous SAARC summits, are implemented.
</P>
<P>
The forcing of children into begging was also a serious problem
in the country and in the rest of South Asia, while malnutrition
was on the rise due to poverty, Jayalath added. 
</P>
