<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
says it is suspending funding for aid projects in the Afghan
capital Kabul because of restrictions imposed by the Taliban
militia.
</P>
<P>
The move by the EC, the biggest aid donor to war-torn
Afghanistan, came after aid agencies were told to move to a
war-ravaged compound on the outskirts of Kabul, the Associated
Press of Pakistan (APP) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
