<HEADLINE> France to Help Nigeria Rid of EU Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- France will encourage other states
of the European Union (EU) to lift sanctions imposed on Nigeria
based on the progress so far made by the country on human rights
and democratization, Foreign Minister Chakles Josseline said.
</P>
<P>
Josseline, who was leading a six-man delegation from France,
gave the assurance in Nigerian capital Abuja after a meeting with
the head of state, General Abdulsalam Abubakar Monday.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that France was watching keenly developments
in Nigeria especially its democratization process, adding that
his country would not set a timetable for Nigeria's transition to
civil rule as it was up to Nigeria to make the decision.
</P>
<P>
Observing that France has had no direct contact at high
government level with Nigeria for the past six years, Josseline
said his visit is an indication of the positive attitude on the
French side toward the new development in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Josseline said he discussed bilateral and African issues with
Abubakar, particularly the need for Nigeria to assist in the
peaceful resolution and prevention of conflicts in Africa.
</P>
<P>
He said the French government had solicited for the
intervention of Nigeria in the resolution of the ongoing crisis
in Guinea Bissau considering the experience of the country in the
resolution of conflicts in Sierra Leone and Liberia.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that he had invited General Abubakar to attend
the France-Africa summit on conflicts resolution coming up in
Paris between November 26 and 28 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
