General Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen people died at the scene and 81 were injured when the
bus they were traveling in plunged 90 meters down an embankment
early on Tuesday morning. A 14th victim was declared dead on
arrival at St. Barnabas Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the two transferred to Umtata, the rest of the
wounded were in a stable condition, according to St. Barnabas
Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police said details of the accident were still scanty and that
police officers were on their way to get more information.
