<HEADLINE> Pak Cotton Sowing Area Crosses 2.9 Mln Hectare Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Minister for Food and
Agriculture Abdul Sattar Lalika said the area under cultivation
for cotton this year has crossed the earlier assessed target of
2.9 million hectares.
</P>
<P>
"Due to increase in cultivation area, we are expecting 10.5
million cotton bales this year," the minister told the reporters
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the target area assessed for cotton cultivation this
year was 2.3 million hectares in Punjab and 600,000 hectares in
Sindh.
</P>
<P>
The latest data collected by the ministry indicates a
reasonable increase in the cotton cultivation area, Lalika noted.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the cotton crop worldwide, Lalika said that the
cotton crop in the United States has been badly damaged. In the
states of Georgia, Texas, Alabama and California, all the cotton
crop has been damaged at the flowering stage.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, India has revised the cotton production target
downward, from 16.8 million bales to 14 million bales, Lalika
said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has very supportive weather conditions and is expected
to earn a hefty amount by exporting cotton this year, according to
Lalika.  
</P>
</TEXT>
