<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The tone is mounting between Albania and Yugoslavia which
have accused each other of violating their sovereignty after the
fighting broke out last weekend on the frontier between Albanian
separatists infiltrating into Kosovo from Albania and the
Yugoslav military, in which 110 people were killed.
</P>
<P>
-- After the doping scandal in the Tour de France cycling
tournament erupted last weekend, some French doctors have
condemned the violation of medical ethics by some medical experts
in sports. They urged a complete ban of drug abuse in any form in
sports and stressed that health, which a doctor is committed to
protecting, must be above sports.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- In France, five million people -- 65 percent of them below
the age of 45 and 20 percent of them women -- are amateurs of
fishing. The Anglo-Saxon tradition of ``no kill'' in fishing,
which let the captured fish return to the water, is gaining
popularity among the French.
</P>
<P>
-- The European Union (EU) Monday urged the Albanian armed
groups in Kosovo and the Yugoslav army to stop fighting
immediately in fear of an escalade of the conflict. The EU
presidency expressed particular concern over the bombardment by
the Yugoslav army on the border with Albania, accusing the latter
of having ``apparently violated the international frontier.''
</P>
