<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, July 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) Monday
announced the approval of a financial support totaling 11.2
billion U.S. dollars for Russia.
</P>
<P>
The financing consists of an augmentation of Russia's extended
arrangement by the equivalent of about 8.3 billion dollars to
support the government's economic program for 1998, and about 2.9
billion dollars under the Compensatory and Contingency Financing
Facility (CCFF) to compensate for a shortfall in export earnings.
(IMF-Financing-Russia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros Pangalos said here
Monday that his country will actively influence Belgrade on the
Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos, who is on a two-day visit to Albania, said Greece
will try to persuade the Yugoslav government to hold talks with
Kosovo ethnic Albanians, with the attendance of representatives
from the international community. (Albania-Greece-Kosovo)
</P>
