<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Elephant Fossils Discovered In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese farmer has
discovered fossils of ivory and bones from an ancient elephant in
north China's Hebei Province, which archaeologists say could date
back 300,000 years.
</P>
<P>
The 3-meter piece of ivory weighs 150 kilograms. It was
discovered in a 12-meter-deep sand pit.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists say that the elephant stood about five meters
tall and was nine meters long.
</P>
<P>
They say that 300,000 years ago the region had a tropical
climate with flowers and trees flourishing. Fossils are of great
importance for research into the movement of the earth's crust in
the Jizhong Plain area and on the evolution of animals.
</P>
<P>
Fossilized ivory and bones were previously discovered in the
same county in 1985 and 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Nations Reach No Consensus on "Flexible Engagement" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The nine member countries of the
Association of Southeast Asian (ASEAN) have not reached a
consensus on a change in ASEAN policy from "non-interference" to
"flexible engagement," a senior official said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN senior officials exchanged views on the "flexible
engagement" at an informal dinner Monday night, but "no consensus
was reached," Philippine Foreign Undersecretary Lauro Baja told a
press briefing on the ASEAN Standing Committee meeting and Senior
Officials Meeting, which opened Tuesday and are scheduled to close
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Only the ministers can decide" whether a change will be made,
Baja added, referring to the foreign ministers who will attend the
31st ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM), also to be held here later
this week.
</P>
<P>
The new proposal means that when domestic developments in an
ASEAN member country have had positive or adverse effects on other
members, other ASEAN nations can give advice to or press the said
country to solve the problems.
</P>
<P>
The idea was raised by Thailand and backed up by the
Philippines. However, senior officials told Xinhua earlier Tuesday
that all the other ASEAN members are "strongly opposed" to the
policy change.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Baja said that during the Standing Committee meeting
and the Senior Officials Meeting, the participants reviewed the
work of ASEAN committees in implementing policies set by the
previous AMM and discussed the agenda for the forthcoming
meetings.
</P>
<P>
The fifth ASEAN Regional Forum and the ASEAN Post-Ministerial
Meetings, two important ASEAN annual events, will also take place
here in the Philippine capital from July 27 to 29.
</P>
<P>
During the 31st AMM, the ministers are expected to sign a joint
declaration on building ASEAN into a region free from drug abuse,
production and trafficking by the year 2020. The new document will
include Laos and Myanmar, the two new members of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Besides Laos and Myanmar, ASEAN also groups Brunei, Indonesia,
Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. The
Philippines is the rotating chairman of ASEAN this year.
</P>
<P>
Besides the drug issue, the ongoing financial crisis and its
social impacts, the Cambodian elections, nuclear proliferation in
South Asia and transnational crimes are also the highlights of the
meetings.
</P>
<P>
Baja added that the ASEAN senior officials would also issue a
statement on the tidal wave in Papua New Guinea which has killed
up to 1,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
