<HEADLINE> Chinese Pangolins Return To Nature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Wild Animal Protection
Administration set two pangolins free in suburban Shanghai
recently.
</P>
<P>
The animal mainly live in mountainous parts of southern China
and are under Category II protection. These two had been captured
in the wild and brought to Shanghai for sale by illegal dealers.
</P>
<P>
The city's police had seized more than 30 of the animals from
dealers. Most of them did not survive the environmental changes,
but 6 were turned over to the Shanghai Zoo.
</P>
<P>
The two freed pangolins had been at the Zoo for two years. They
will live on Sheshan Mountain near Shanghai for a period of time
and researchers will keep track of them through radio
transmitters. Then they will be completely on their own after they
have adapted to the natural environment.
</P>
<P>
The 4 remaining pangolins will be set free soon, and a wild
animal rescue center will be established on Sheshan Mountain to
offer protection for illegally captured wild animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
