<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Cooperation With Other Countries In Offshore Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Even with a large number of
contracts with oil giants from 18 countries, China still needs
more foreign cooperation in offshore oil and gas exploration,
according to Lin Shaodong, president of the China National
Offshore Oil Bohai Corp (CNOOBC).
</P>
<P>
China is rich in offshore oil and gas, with proven offshore
reserves of one billion tons and 200 billion
cu.m. respectively. But, estimates reach as high as 25 billion
tons and 14 trillion cu m, respectively.
</P>
<P>
So, it is only by dramatically increasing Sino-foreign
cooperation that China can speed up offshore oil and gas
development, Lin says, and foreign oil giants have shown an
interest in investing in China's offshore oil and gas exploration,
and have already put 6.4 billion U.S. dollars into it.
</P>
<P>
Through joint efforts, China has drilled nearly 400 exploratory
wells, and verified nearly 100 oil- and gas-bearing structures with
deposits of 1.2 billion tons and 180 billion cu.m., respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the Bohai and Yingge seas and the Beibu Bay, there are 19
operational oilfields, with annual oil and gas output of 16
million tons and 4 billion cu.m., respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Battlefield Discovered In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A farmer in north China's
Hebei Province recently stumbled onto human remains and some
bronze weapons along a dike, which local archaeologists say is the
site of a battle that took place more than 2,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The archaeologists later found more remains, many with broken
swords in hands. The longest was a double-edged sword, 37.4 cm
long, they report.
</P>
<P>
Animal skeletons and bronze weapons were found scattered along
a kilometer stretch of the dike, which is one of the world's three
longest and oldest dikes.
</P>
<P>
They also discovered three tombs in the area with pottery,
jars, pots, and basins in them and unearthed 14 urns used as
coffins for children.  
</P>
</TEXT>
