<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scientists: Vitamin B-6 May Decrease Heart Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 20 (Xinhua) -- People with the highest levels
of vitamin B-6 have only 30 percent of the risk of heart disease
compared to those with the lowest levels, said a study released
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The study, conducted by researchers of the University of
Minnesota and reported in the latest issue of the American Heart
Association Journal Circulation, started out with 759 people aged
45 to 64 between 1987 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
"Among the 759 volunteers, 232 developed heart disease at
different stages," said Aaron Folsom, heading the research group.
All the volunteers had given blood samples which were frozen for
analysis, he added.
</P>
<P>
The next step, according to Folsom, should involve giving some
people vitamin B-6 supplements, and other people placebos, to see
if that affects the rates of heart disease.
</P>
<P>
In February, researchers wrote in the Journal of the American
Medical Association that women who had high intakes of vitamin B-6
and another B vitamin, folic acid, had a 45 percent lower risk of
heart disease.
</P>
<P>
Researchers said vitamin B-6 is naturally rich in wheat germ,
soybeans, peanuts, bananas and other foods. They recommend people
eating plenty of fruits and vegetables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Repairs on Beijing's Tian'anmen Square </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's Tian'anmen Square, the
scene of many momentous events over the past half century, is
going to get a facelift starting October in preparation for the
50th anniversary celebrations of the People's Republic to be held
on October 1 next year.
</P>
<P>
The bricks and loud-speaker system, which was installed in
1959, are showing their age and will be changed. Workers already
changed more than 20,000 square meters of bricks last year, but
old bricks are wearing out fast. All cement bricks on a
170,000-square-meter area will be replaced with wear-resistant
granite bricks, which have a life expectancy of at least 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Many of the loud-speakers on poles around the square are broken
or have become sparrow nests and need to be replaced.
</P>
<P>
Lighting has been a major problem for a long time. Four tall
lightpoles were put up for the celebration of Hong Kong's
returning to China last year, but the move was criticized by some
people for spoiling the square's appearance.
</P>
<P>
Some engineers have suggested that the tall poles be taken down
and the old dim lights replaced with bright ones. The lights on
the square's major buildings like the rostrum, the Great Hall of
the People, the Museum of Chinese History, the Museum of the
Chinese Revolution, and the Monument to the People's Heroes need
to be improved to highlight them.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a fountain, 70 meters in diameter, and equipped
with laser lights, will be built between the monument and the
national flag pole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5m People Suffer from Goiter in Northern Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- About 5 million people have been
suffering from goiter due to iodine deficiency in the northern
part of Bangladesh, an English daily here reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Deficiency of iodine is causing the spread of diseases like
mental and physical disability, dwarfness, less IQ (intelligence
quotient) and infant mortality in 16 districts of the country's
northern region of Pabna, The Bangladesh Observer quoted a medical
source as saying.
</P>
<P>
Iodine was available in sea creatures and land adjacent to the
sea, but it lacks in the land of the country's northern districts,
the source said, adding that besides, rainfall and flood water
washed away the natural ingredient every year from the land
specially in flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the crops produced on the land cannot supply
required quantity of iodine.
</P>
<P>
The use of iodized salt is one of the means to get rid of the
diseases but the businessmen are marketing salt without iodine
taking the advantage of the lack of awareness of the people in the
region.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, a group of people of the society prefer
non-iodized salt due to low price which is being smuggled into the
country from India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980721.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Extract Protein From Fly Larvae </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
discovered a protein that could be important for domestic animal
breeding and pharmaceutical production that they extracted from
maggots.
</P>
<P>
Scientists at Southwest China Agricultural University's Biology
Institute in the city of Chongqing say the extract has proven to
be useful for a kind of high-quality fodder and could be used to
produce tonics and pharmaceutical products.
</P>
<P>
They said that the maggot powder fodder caused female chickens
to lay 20 percent more eggs than those fed with fish powder and it
can be used to help pigs put on weight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
