<HEADLINE> WB Likely to Provide Malaysia 7m U.S. Dollars Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank, supportive of
Malaysia's request for another loan of 700 million U.S. dollars,
is likely to disburse the loan before the end of the year to
support the country's social programs, Malaysia's national news
agency Bernama reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 700 million U.S. dollars loan is particularly important as
the economic downturn had increased the number of hard-core poor,
"and our target is to eradicate the hard-core poor," Bernama
quoted Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim as telling
reporters in Washington Monday.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank recently approved and disbursed to Malaysia a
loan of 300 million U.S. dollars for the implementation of social
programs that include poverty eradication, agriculture, education
and medical facilities. The concessionary loan extended by the
bank is payable in 15 years. 
</P>
