<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Customs Stopping Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The customs office in the capital
of Hainan, China's southernmost province, cracked 41 cases of
smuggling that were worth 43 million yuan in the first six months
of this year.
</P>
<P>
The illicit goods were refined oil products, antimony ingots,
wine, cars and car parts, cellular phones, and pagers.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers discovered the illegal goods in containers and
on boats to and from Hong Kong and Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
