<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Wins Over China in Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. team, composed mostly by young players aged between
20 and 23,felt more at home in front of thousands of fans at
the  Madison Square Garden in Manhattan. The junior national
team lost  the opening game to Puerto Rico Sunday. The loss
forced the U.S. players to fight to win the remaining games
with China Monday and Brazil Tuesday if they want to make the
semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Compared with their younger counterparts, the Chinese
players seemed to be too cautious in their offensive attacks
and showed no advantage in rebounds. The Americans led the
halftime by only two points, 49-47.
</P>
<P>
Although China's sharpshooter Zhang Jinsong and veteran
player  Adi-Jiang did not appear at the second half, the Chinese
still managed to draw even by 66: 66 at about the 13th minute.
But the Chinese showed their fatigueness and made more mistakes
later, which led to their final loss.
</P>
<P>
China lost to Brazil Sunday, having no chance to enter the
semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
In other three games Monday, Russia beat Australia by 78-73.
Both teams got one point.
</P>
<P>
Brazil beat Puerto Rico by 96-92, with Brazil gaining 2
points, Puerto Rico, one point.
</P>
<P>
And Argentina lost to Lithuania, 77 to 81 and have no points
to their credit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
