<HEADLINE> hke072124 -Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Plan To Mislead SAARC Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's intelligence has
reported that the Tamil rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) are planning to mislead SAARC leaders due to attend
this month's summit here, defense sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE is planning to hand over a memorandum defamatory of
the Sri Lanka government and the security forces to the leaders of
the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC).
</P>
<P>
The memorandum is to be presented to the Leaders by a bogus
non-governmental organization, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum will aim to expose the Sri Lanka government as
trying to massacre the entire Tamil race; that the security forces
have been indiscriminately bombing civilian targets; Tamil
civilians are indiscriminately harassed, detained and tortured and
some Tamils disappear without a trace.
</P>
<P>
A Defense Ministry official said that the Tamil community would
not believe these ravings of the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a war against the government for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
