<HEADLINE> hke072125 -Western Bloc Threatens Myanmar Through Media: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A Myanmar minister has accused the
Western Bloc of threatening his country through the mass media.
</P>
<P>
"The West Bloc and their media are trying to disturb stability,
disrupt economy and unity and incite unrest in countries which do
not accept their influence," Major-General Kyi Aung, minister of
information was quoted by Tuesday's official newspaper The New
Light of Myanmar as saying.
</P>
<P>
"In so doing, they attempt to worsen the situation and apply
pressure," the minister noted when meeting with information and
public relations officers under training here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The minister also stressed the need to safeguard the national
character in the light of widespread penetration of the
international media.
</P>
<P>
He added that the ministry will provide the media personnel
with training at a time when the Age of Information or
Information Super Highway is being established. 
