<HEADLINE> EU to Provide Romania with Water Conservancy Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The Europe Union has decided to
provide a loan of 50 million ECU (about 45 million U.S. dollars)
for Romania's water conservancy projects, said the Romanian Water,
Forests and Environmental Protection Ministry on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The low-interest loan with a 10-year maturity term will be used
in water conservancy projects, renovation of flood-destroyed
forest roads and installation of early-warning radar equipment.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian government will provide guarantee for the loan.
</P>
<P>
Romania needs to invest at least 11,000 billion leu (1.26
billion U.S. dollars) in flood control projects, but the
government cannot afford the sum, Minister of Water, Forests and
Environmental Protection Ro MicaTomescu said.
</P>
<P>
The Water Conservancy Ministry's budget this year is only 340
billion leu (39 million dollars), representing only 0.059 percent
of the country's GDP, he added.
</P>
<P>
The direct loss caused by the severe floods this year is
estimated at 1,280 billion leu (147 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
