<HEADLINE> Dhaka Fixes Manpower Export Target for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Committee of the
Bangladesh's National Economic council on Monday approved a
proposed target of manpower export for the year 1998, a press
report said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the current year, the country will export some 222,500
Bangladeshi workers to different countries, according to the
target.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 120,000 will be exported to Saudi Arabia, 22,400
to the United Arab Emirates, 15,000 to Kuwait and 25,000 to
Singapore, while the rest will go to some other Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh exported 205,200 workers last year.
</P>
<P>
Manpower export is one of the major foreign exchange earners
for the South Asian country. About 1.53 billion U.S. dollars in
remittances were sent back home in 1997 as against 1.36 billion
dollars in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
