<HEADLINE> Canada Welcomes Nigeria's Democracy Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Canada Monday welcomed an
announcement by General Abdulsalam Abubakar that Nigeria would
have a democratically elected, civilian government by May 29, 1999.
</P>
<P>
It also welcomed the general's decision to release all
political prisoners.
</P>
<P>
"It is clear that General Abubakar has listened to the Nigerian
people's demands for democracy. We are prepared to work with the
Nigerians as they bring these changes into effect," said Foreign
Minister Lloyd Axworthy in a statement.
</P>
