<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus Wins Men's All-around Gymnastics Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Ivan Ivankov of Belarus took the
gold medal in the men's all around individual gymnastics
at the fourth Goodwill Games in Long Island, New York on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ivankov claimed the victory by scoring a total of 57.500 points
in the six apparatuses, 9.300 from floor exercise, 9.650 from
pummel horse, 9.750 from rings, 9.450 from vault, 9.775 from
parallel bars and 9.575 from horizontal bar.
</P>
<P>
"It was not bad," Ivankov told a press briefing after the
competitions. "Winning the gold medal in the world championships
and the Goodwill Games is my next step to the next Olympics," said
the happy Ivankov.
</P>
<P>
He got 0.8 more points than the second place finisher, Alexel
Bondarenko, who received a total of 56.700 points.
</P>
<P>
Bondarenko, who got only 8.950 points in the floor exercise,
said, "I would like to have performed better. ... I feel
very down emotionally. But I will accept the second place."
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal was carried by America's Blaine Wilson with
56.575 points. He said that it was as good as he expected since he
had a shoulder injury.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 athletes from eight countries performed their
routines in the events. Ukrane's Roman Zozulia finished fourth
with 56.450 points and China's Lu Yufu finished fifth with
56.250. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
