<HEADLINE> Waller Wins Women's High Jump Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Tisha Waller of the United States
cleared 1.97 meters to win the women's high jump gold in the
athletics competition of the Goodwill Games here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Waller, U.S. champion this season, beat her teammate Amy Acuff
and Yuliya Lyakhova of Russia, both finished at 1.93 meters and
shared the second place.
</P>
<P>
Waller, 28, cleared over the hights from 1.80 to 1.97 all in
her first try, failed to jump over 2.01 in three times.
</P>
<P>
Acuff, World University Games winner and Lyakhova, world junior
champion in 1996, started at the same height and cleared all their
heights before they failed three times at 1.97. 
