<HEADLINE> Sadova Wins Women's Discus Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Natalya Sadova of Russia tossed
65.80 meters to win the women's discus in the athletics
competition of the Goodwill Games here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ilke Wyludda of Germany finished second with a throw of 63.03,
and Kristin Kuehl of the United States wound up third at 61.84.
</P>
<P>
Sadova, Olympic silver medalist and world bronze winner last
year, led the first round with a 62.82 heave, followed by Wyludda,
Olympic champion and world silver medalist, at 62.70.
</P>
<P>
Sadova got her winner in the second round. Barbara Hechevarria
of Cuba, the defending champion, finished fifth with a poor 58.98
finish. 
</P>
