<HEADLINE> Pedroso Wins Men's Long Jump Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Ivan Pedroso of Cuba won the
men's long jump gold medal as expected when the world champion
jumped 8.54 meters in the athletics competition of the Goodwill
Games in LongIsland, New York, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Erick Walder of the United States won the silver with an 8.38
leap and James Beckford of Jamaica took the bronze at 8.34.
</P>
<P>
Pedroso, 26, fouled his first two jumps before registering an
8.21 leap in his third. He landed his longest distance in the
fifth outing, fouling the fourth and the last.
</P>
<P>
Walder, world silver medalist, beat Beckford with his final
effort with a slight tail wind. Beckford, Olympic silver medalist,
led the field with a second-round 8.34 leap till Pedroso produced
his winner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
