<HEADLINE> Dini: Solve Guinea Bissau Crisis Within the Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Efforts to solve the crisis in Guinea
Bissau should be sought within that region, Italian Foreign
Minister Lamberto Dini said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meeting his Senegalese counterpart Jacques Baudin, Dini voiced
concern over the situation in the small Western African state.
</P>
<P>
A rebellion erupted on June 7 after President Joao
Bernardo Vieira sacked armed forces chief General Ansumane
Mane.
</P>
<P>
Now more than 250,000 people have fled the fighting, and it
is difficult for the humanitarian aid to reach them.
</P>
<P>
Baudin said Senegal playing a major role in solving the crisis
will try to ensure that the humanitarian aid reach those who need it.
</P>
<P>
Italy is sending some 300,000 U.S. dollars in aid through the
International Red Cross to the area.
</P>
<P>
Also the ministers discussed ways to promote bilateral trade
and signed an agreement on avoiding double taxation.
</P>
<P>
Italy is Senegal's third largest importer after France and
Spain.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are expected to sign an agreement on
protection of investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
