<HEADLINE> O'Brien Wins Decathlon but Misses World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 20 (Xinhua) -- World record holder Dan O'Brien
of the United States won the men's decathlon gold but just missed
to break the world record at the Goodwill Games here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The American collected 8,755 points, only 136 points shy of his
world record. But he beat the meet record of 8,715 and earned
40,000 U.S. dollars bonus.
</P>
<P>
The silver and bronze medals were won by Chris Huffins of the
United States and Tomas Dvorak of Czech Republic respectively.
Huffins, U.S. champion with a personal best of 8,694, scored 8,576
and Dvorak got 8,428. 
</P>
</TEXT>
