<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Kills More Than 10 People in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Heat wave has killed more than
10 people in northern Mexico and left 200 more people suffering
from sunstroke.
</P>
<P>
Reports said on Monday that the area has been under a heat wave
of 49 Celsius degrees for several days.
</P>
<P>
In Lower California, especially in the desert city of Mexicali,
the number of people suffering sunstroke has been climbing and
throwing many emergency rooms into chaos.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 people have been sent to hospitals for emergency
treatment because of sunstroke and dehydration, of whom eight
people died for late attendance.
</P>
<P>
In the state of Sonora, the temperature reaches a record high
of 49 degrees in the shades. At least four adults have been killed
by sunstroke.
</P>
<P>
The local medical department has issued an urgent warning to
the residents, asking them to take all kinds of precaution
measures. 
</P>
