<HEADLINE> Car Sales Fall Sharply in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Car sales in Indonesia plunged
82.4 percent in the first half of this year, the Jakarta Post
Tuesday quoted industry statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
The statistics, provided by the country's largest carmaker PT
Astra International, showed that car sales for the first half of
the year plunged to 35,789 units, sharply lower than the 203,212
units sold during the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Astra and the country's other largest carmaker PT Indomobil
Sukses Makmur have halted production due to the slump in domestic
demand, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Indonesian Automotive Industries said last
week there were still 40,000 new cars in stock.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also said motorcycle sales fell 70 percent to
258,151 for the first half of the year from 858,353 in the same
period last year.  
</P>
