<HEADLINE> Ten Chinese Provinces Report Farmland Soaked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Heavy flooding in various parts of
China has turned 4.19 million ha of farmland in 10 provinces and
autonomous regions into extremely wet ground, the State Flood
Control and Drought Relief Headquarters reports.
</P>
<P>
Of that area, 642,900 ha are expected to have total crop
failures this year, agronomists say.
</P>
<P>
Governments of the 10 provinces have gathered a massive amount
of machinery to drain the fields, and have moved 19.3 billion
cubic meters of water from 3.48 million ha of land, and farmers
are working hard to plant late rice.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Province, a major rice grower, has got enough
machinery to pump water from all its soaked fields, while Anhui,
Hunan and Guangdong have also had some success in this.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi Province and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region are
lagging behind because of a fear that excessive drainage would
pose a threat to river banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
