<HEADLINE> Explosives Found in Bus Bound For Sri Lanka's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Three parcels of explosives were
found in a bus bound for Sri Lanka's capital city Colombo from
Negombo 35 kilometers from here, according to police here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
When army personnel detected the explosives at a check point at
Wattala, a suburb of Colombo, in addition to the explosives they
also found two handgrenades with their pins off and covered with
cellophane tape.
