<HEADLINE> Chinese Intelligent Information Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- China has developed an intelligent
information network, CIN03, which passed final assessment in
Shanghai last Friday that connects with China's intelligent
telecommunications network better than foreign systems.
</P>
<P>
The system adds computer controls to the conventional
telecommunications network for speed and convenience.
</P>
<P>
CIN03 was developed by Beijing's Posts and Telecommunications
University, the former Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications'
Transmitting Technology Institute, and Shanghai's Posts and
Telecommunications Administration.
</P>
<P>
The system has already been used in Shanghai's
telecommunications network where it added things like a debit
telephone card and collect calls to the old network.
</P>
<P>
A Ministry of the Information Industry official says that China
has taken an important step forward in commercializing its
intelligent information network using its own intellectual
property.
</P>
<P>
The network is one of the key projects of the national
scientific and technological development program.  
</P>
