<HEADLINE> Cruise Ship on Fire Offshore Miami </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Black smoke billowed Monday
from the stern of a Carnival cruise ship two miles offshore before
crews were able to contain flames shooting from portholes,
according to local media here.
</P>
<P>
No injuries have been reported and a tugboat pulled the ship
Ecstasy back to Miami, after the fire appeared to be contained in
about two hours.
</P>
