<HEADLINE> Fashion Through Chinese Eyes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- More than half the people of
China regard fashion as something a bit avant-garde, according to
a recent survey of 1,500 citizens in large Chinese cities like
Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou, and some 5,400 Internet users.
</P>
<P>
Fashion was regarded as avant-garde by 55 percent of the
respondents, while 22 percent said that fashion is a natural,
attractive, and cultural accomplishment.
</P>
<P>
Another 7 percent thought that fashion follows trends and 5
percent said that the wealthy and powerful are fashionable.
</P>
<P>
In answer to "What is fashionable", most said new
entertainment, exaggerated clothing, and being wealthy enough to
enjoy a colorful life.
</P>
<P>
A major index for fashion is whether one owns high-tech
products and cosmetics and has a new life style. 
</P>
</TEXT>
