<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Exports Down in Dollars, Up in Baht </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports in U.S. dollar
terms, fell by 4.4 percent during the first five months of this
year compared to the same period last year, but in terms of baht,
rose by 63.5 percent, according to figures issued by the Thai
Commerce Ministry available Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Exports in baht terms totaled 983,375 million baht, while in
dollar terms exports were worth 22,306 million.
</P>
<P>
For the period, Thailand imported goods 791,621 million baht,
a 6.1 percent increase from last year. However, in dollar terms,
imports fell sharply by 38.3 percent to 17,759 million.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's trade balance in baht terms over the first five
months of this year was recorded at 191.754 million baht, while
that in dollar terms was 4,547 million.
</P>
<P>
In May, the value of monthly exports totaled 4,328 million
U.S. dollars, down 11.8 percent from the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's major trade partners remained the United States,
European Union, other ASEAN nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
