<HEADLINE> Masterkova Wins Women's Mile Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Svetlana Masterkova of Russia
beat two U.S. rivals on the home straight to win the women's mile
gold medal in the athletics competition of the Goodwill Games here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Masterkova, world record holder and Olympic 800 meters winner,
clocked 4 minute 20.39 seconds for the title, well outside of her
personal best 4:12.56.
</P>
<P>
Regina Jacobs romped home second in 4:20.93 and Suzy Hamilton
taped in 4:22.93.
</P>
<P>
Sonia O'Sullivan of Ireland, world 1,500 runner up and 5,000
champion in 1995, finished fifth in 4:26.19.
</P>
<P>
Jacobs opened a blistering fast pace from the very beginning,
dropping the field 10 meters in her wake after one lap. But three
minutes into the race, Masterkova and Hamilton caught her.
</P>
<P>
The three accerelated at the bell and Masterkova changed to a
higher gear on the final curve, with the two runners hanging
closely.
</P>
<P>
On the home stretch, Masterkova kicked hard to win the race
with at least three meters to spare. 
</P>
</TEXT>
