<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies With Flood Damage Get Insurance Compensation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A subsidiary of the People's
Insurance Co. Ltd of south China's Guangdong Province has paid out
more than 30 million yuan in indemnities in areas of the province
that were hit by floods.
</P>
<P>
The money is being used to restore production in companies that
had flood damage.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains have hit much of southern China since late
June, causing water levels in the Xijiang and Beijiang, two of
Guangdong's main rivers, to rise.
</P>
<P>
Flooding is reported to have caused losses of more than 200
million yuan worth of property covered by insurance in some 30
cities and counties in the province.
</P>
<P>
In the towns of Xijiao and Danzao, insured enterprises have
got 11.8 million yuan in indemnities, which has helped 20
companies to resume production.  
