<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Raises Taxes to Decrease Budgetary Deficit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The taxes are to be raised in
Romania due to the increased budgetary deficit, informed sources
of the Finance Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The budgetary deficit increased beyond the expectations in the
first semester of this year. Therefore, the government has to find
new resources to keep the budgetary deficit within the 3.6 percent
of GDP limit as it was stated in the agreements signed with the
International Monetary Fund and the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 budget, which was adopted in May this year, would have
to be revised in August.
</P>
<P>
During the budget alteration, the ministry would make cuts on
budgetary expenses at all state institutions as well as the
companies subsidized by the state, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Without specifying neither the tax raise percentage nor the tax
categories which would be raised, advisor to the Finance Minister
Cornel Tirhoaca stated that "at present, there are categories of
taxes which are lower than in other countries."
</P>
<P>
He added that the tax raise would increase the budget by 3
percent of the GDP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
