<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Catches More Illegal Immigrants Than Before </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The number of illegal immigrants
caught trying to sneak into Britain had risen from 330 a month
last year to 550 a month this year, the government said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We don't know whether more people are coming through or
whether we are being more successful catching them," a Home Office
(interior ministry) spokeswoman told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"People are coming in from the (European) continent on freight
lorries, but they may have originated from anywhere and come in as
a part of a trafficking route," she said.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokeswoman, police last week disarmed 15
Turkish Kurd immigrants who retaliated with screwdrivers and
broken bottles after they were found to have stowed away on a
ferry to the port of Folkestone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
